The present invention will be further described with reference to the figures of the drawing, wherein:
Figure 1 is a diagrammatic view of a therapy delivery system in accordance with one embodiment of the invention, the system having a therapy delivery device (e.g., therapy catheter), an exemplary body portal anchor (e.g., a burr hole anchor), and, optionally, a therapy source (e.g., an infusion pump) and delivery or feed device (e.g., delivery catheter);
Figure 2 is an enlarged perspective view of a burr hole anchor in accordance with one embodiment of the invention;
Figure 3 is an exploded perspective view of the burr hole anchor of Figure 2;
Figure 4 is a perspective view of the anchor of Figure 2 with a shearing mechanism, e.g., door, of the anchor shown in an open position;
Figure 5 is a perspective view of the apparatus of Figure 2 with the door of the anchor shown in a closed position;
Figures 6A-6B illustrate bottom perspective views of the anchor of Figure 2, wherein: Figure 6A is a view of the whole anchor; and Figure 6B is an exploded view of an insert or module of the anchor;
Figure 7 is an enlarged perspective view of a burr hole anchor in accordance with another embodiment of the invention;
Figure 8 is an exploded perspective view of the anchor of Figure 7;
Figure 9 is a bottom perspective view of the anchor of Figure 7 with a clip attached;
Figures 10A-10C illustrate a method of using the anchor of Figure 7, wherein: Figure 10A is a perspective view with a shearing mechanism, e.g., door, of the anchor shown in an open position and with a clip attached, the shearing mechanism shown prior to shearing the therapy catheter; Figure 10B is a perspective view with the door shown in a closed position after shearing the catheter; and Figure 10C is a perspective view with the door shown in a closed position and the clip removed;
Figures 11A-11B are cross-sectional views of the anchor of Figure 7, wherein: Figure 11A shows the connector of the anchor in a first or uncoupled position; and Figure 11B shows the connector in a second or coupled position;
Figure 12 is a perspective view of a burr hole anchor in accordance with another embodiment of the invention;
Figure 13 is a perspective view of an exemplary base of the anchor of Figure 12;
Figure 14 is an exploded perspective view of an exemplary catheter connection module for use with the anchor of Figure 12;
Figure 15 is a partial perspective section view of the assembled catheter connection module of Figure 14 as it may be attached to the base of Figure 13;
Figure 16 is a top perspective view of the anchor of Figure 12 as assembled and with a cap attached;
Figure 17 is a bottom perspective view of the anchor of Figure 12 with the cap detached;
Figure 18 is a side elevation view of the anchor of Figure 12 with a shearing mechanism, e.g., door, shown in the open position and the cap removed;
Figure 19 is a top perspective view of an alternative embodiment of the anchor of Figure 12;
Figure 20 is a perspective view of a burr hole anchor in accordance with yet another embodiment of the invention;
Figure 21 is a partial exploded perspective view of the anchor of Figure 20; and
Figure 22 is a section view of a therapy catheter in accordance with one embodiment of the invention that may be utilized with the exemplary systems, apparatus, and methods described herein.
